Area: a collection of regions
  name
  bits
  region-list-head
  next-area

Region: a region of memory with a storage type (structure or list), and gc info
  origin        base address of the region (word address as fixnum)
  length        number of words in the region
  free-pointer
  bits          various flag bits
  next-region   next region in the chain (sorted?)


Initial areas:
  support-area           Holds NIL, T, the undefined-function function,
                         directly-called helper functions and initial
                         area/region data.
  function-area          Compiled functions, a static area.
  interrupt-area         Wired data used by interrupts or dma, etc. A static area.
  runtime-data-area      General use area. The default allocation area.
